This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the task of Salient Object Detection (SOD) using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs). Additionally, the paper also discusses the comparison between two different CNN architectures, which falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of deep learning techniques in the paper also suggests the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image processing and analysis, which falls under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
